{"body":"### Current Behavior

On a desired normal scenario, people are free to update vscode and get needed extensions. Currently I'm not in that scope as due for work reasons I'm locked to vscode 1.90.2

With that in mind, I can't use the Nx console visual migration tool on an old version of vscode.

![Image](https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/c77ea326-9782-4ab4-9dcb-d048020a8f7c)

### Expected Behavior

Not sure if it is because of API on VSCode that version is locked up to be compatible on versions above 1.90.2.

### GitHub Repo

_No response_

